## Definition

A **sylleptic $\infty$-group** is an [[âˆž-group]] $G$ equipped with the following equivalent [[structure]]

1. a lift of its [[A-âˆž algebra|A-âˆž]]/[[E-n algebra|E1]]-algebra structure to an [[E-n algebra|E3]] algebra structure;

1. the structure of a [[braided âˆž-group]] on its [[delooping]] $\mathbf{B}G$

1. the structure of an [[âˆž-group]] on its double [[delooping]] $\mathbf{B}^2 G$

1. a triple [[delooping]] $\mathbf{B}^3 G$.

